<subSubSection id="1C8A6552A501892C8CE74E588B90337A" pageId="31" pageNumber="304" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="542F36D9A501892C8CE74E588B9230BA" blockId="31.[151,756,1897,2081]" lastBlockId="31.[793,1398,233,609]" pageId="31" pageNumber="304">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA501892C8CE74E58890E369A" bold="true" box="[151,258,1897,1921]" pageId="31" pageNumber="304">Remarks:</emphasis>
A small, dainty species, reminiscent of 
<taxonomicName id="93904D5AA501892C8CE74EBB890436BA" baseAuthorityName="ALFKEN" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[151,264,1929,1953]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trifidus">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA501892C8CE74EBB890436BA" box="[151,264,1929,1953]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="304">H. trifidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the shape of the mask: the tip of the lateral marks is at the level of the antenna bases; in the upper part they are separated from the compound eye margin by an impressed shiny surface. In 
<taxonomicName id="93904D5AA501892C8EF44EDB8AF8391A" baseAuthorityName="ALFKEN" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[644,756,2025,2049]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trifidus">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA501892C8EF44EDB8AF8391A" box="[644,756,2025,2049]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="304">H. trifidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
this surface is oval and clearly defined, in 
<taxonomicName id="93904D5AA501892C8E07413B8AF8393A" baseAuthorityName="WARNCKE" baseAuthorityYear="1992" box="[631,756,2057,2081]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="funereus">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA501892C8E07413B8AF8393A" box="[631,756,2057,2081]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="304">H. funereus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
there is a blurred furrow extended upward along the orbits. The apical process of sternum 8 is conoid with lateral bristles, in 
<taxonomicName id="93904D5AA501892C8F90481B8C5C305A" baseAuthorityName="ALFKEN" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[992,1104,297,321]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trifidus">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA501892C8F90481B8C5C305A" box="[992,1104,297,321]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="304">H. trifidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with expanded lobus with V-shaped notch; in this structure 
<taxonomicName id="93904D5AA501892C88F6487B8D08307A" baseAuthorityName="WARNCKE" baseAuthorityYear="1992" box="[1158,1284,329,353]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="funereus">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA501892C88F6487B8D08307A" box="[1158,1284,329,353]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="304">H. funereus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles more 
<taxonomicName id="93904D5AA501892C8F28485B8BC0309A" baseAuthorityName="WARNCKE" baseAuthorityYear="1981" box="[856,972,361,385]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Prosopis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="31" pageNumber="304" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sidensis">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA501892C8F28485B8BC0309A" box="[856,972,361,385]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="304">H. sidensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The propodeum is rounded and without ringlets.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="542F36D9A501892C8F69489B8B90337A" blockId="31.[793,1398,233,609]" pageId="31" pageNumber="304">
<taxonomicName id="93904D5AA501892C8F69489B8B9E30DA" baseAuthorityName="WARNCKE" baseAuthorityYear="1992" box="[793,914,425,449]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="funereus">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA501892C8F69489B8B9E30DA" box="[793,914,425,449]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="304">H. funereus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<materialsCitation id="E4F83C84A501892C8FEB489B8B9B337A" collectionCode="VII" country="Turkey" county="It" elevation="1850" location="Unfortunately" municipality="The" pageId="31" pageNumber="304" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Hakkari">
was described from 
<collectingRegion id="9654F83BA501892C880848988CC330DA" box="[1144,1231,425,449]" country="Turkey" name="Hakkari" pageId="31" pageNumber="304">Hakkâri</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="9654F83BA501892C897748988D7930DA" box="[1287,1397,425,449]" country="Turkey" name="Adiyaman" pageId="31" pageNumber="304">Adıyaman</collectingRegion>
(
<quantity id="93689B3CA501892C8F5048F88BB930FA" box="[800,949,457,481]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="31" pageNumber="304" unit="m" value="1850.0" valueMax="2500.0" valueMin="1200.0">
<elevation id="DFBDD1EAA501892C8F5048F88BB930FA" box="[800,949,457,481]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="31" pageNumber="304" unit="m" value="1850.0" valueMax="2500.0" valueMin="1200.0">1200–2500 m</elevation>
</quantity>
). 
<location id="514F6002A501892C8FB648F88C5130FA" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:DC3987CFA501892C8CCD4FA28CD333BA:514F6002A501892C8FB648F88C5130FA" box="[966,1117,457,481]" country="Turkey" county="It" municipality="The" name="Unfortunately" pageId="31" pageNumber="304" stateProvince="Hakkari">Unfortunately</location>
no additional material has been collected since then. 
<collectingMunicipality id="B44BACA3A501892C884C48D88C6A331A" box="[1084,1126,489,513]" pageId="31" pageNumber="304">The</collectingMunicipality>
available data show that 
<taxonomicName id="93904D5AA501892C8F694B3B8B9E333A" baseAuthorityName="WARNCKE" baseAuthorityYear="1992" box="[793,914,521,545]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="funereus">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA501892C8F694B3B8B9E333A" box="[793,914,521,545]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="304">H. funereus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to the south-eastern part of the country. 
<collectingCounty id="BD4E4E55A501892C8F0A4B1B8B86335A" box="[890,906,554,577]" pageId="31" pageNumber="304">It</collectingCounty>
is rarely recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="2C877649A501892C88E94B188CE8335A" box="[1177,1252,553,577]" name="Turkey" pageId="31" pageNumber="304">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(2 provinces, 
<figureCitation id="CCAB2A5CA501892C8F694B788B6E337A" box="[793,866,585,609]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="68.[211,244,1429,1451]" captionTargetBox="[211,1414,859,1420]" captionTargetId="figure-259@68.[211,1414,859,1420]" captionTargetPageId="68" captionText="Fig. 17: Distribution map of rarely recorded Hylaeus species in Turkey: species collected in only one (1-12) or two (II-X)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5742935" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5742935/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="304">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
. 
<collectionCode id="3281AE1CA501892C8F154B788B83337A" box="[869,911,585,609]" pageId="31" pageNumber="304">VII</collectionCode>
)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
